        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 14 at 4:18PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 418 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area favorable for
thunderstorm development and possible landsouts, extending from 12
miles northeast of Rockport to over Lochbuie, or extending from 39
miles northeast of Fort Collins to 23 miles northeast of Denver,
moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greeley, Brighton, Windsor, Evans, Fort Lupton, Milliken,
Lochbuie, Eaton, Severance, Platteville, Hudson, LaSalle, Ault,
Gilcrest, Pierce, Nunn, Lucerne, Purcell, Milton Reservoir and
Garden City.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If a tornado is spotted seek shelter inside a sturdy building.</instruction>
